
[1]learning

   LEARNING, ppr. lern'ing. Gaining knowledge by instruction or reading,
   by study, by experience or observation; acquiring skill by practice.

   LEARNING, n. lern'ing.

   1. The knowledge of principles or facts received by instruction or
   study; acquired knowledge or ideas in any branch of science or
   literature; erudition; literature; science. The Scaligers were men of
   great learning.

   [This is the proper sense of the word.]

   2. Knowledge acquired by experience, experiment or observation.

   3. Skill in anything good or bad.
